            <div class="border border-gray-200 rounded-lg p-6">
              <h3 class="font-semibold text-gray-900 mb-3">
                How often does Scout check for new matches?
              </h3>
              <p class="text-gray-600">
                Scout automatically checks for new matches every minute. When a
                tracked player starts a match, you'll get a notification within
                1-2 minutes.
              </p>
            </div>

            <div class="border border-gray-200 rounded-lg p-6">
              <h3 class="font-semibold text-gray-900 mb-3">
                What types of matches are tracked?
              </h3>
              <p class="text-gray-600">
                Scout tracks all ranked and normal games on Summoner's Rift,
                ARAM, Arena (2v2v2v2v2v2v2v2), and other matchmade queues.
                Custom games, practice tool, and tutorial matches are not
                tracked.
              </p>
            </div>

            <div class="border border-gray-200 rounded-lg p-6">
              <h3 class="font-semibold text-gray-900 mb-3">
                How do competitions work?
              </h3>
              <p class="text-gray-600">
                Competitions allow you to create time-limited challenges for
                your server members. You can set custom criteria (wins, KDA,
                damage, etc.) and Scout will automatically track performance and
                update leaderboards. Use <code
                  class="bg-gray-100 px-2 py-1 rounded text-sm"
                  >/competition create</code
                > to get started!
              </p>
            </div>

            <div class="border border-gray-200 rounded-lg p-6">
              <h3 class="font-semibold text-gray-900 mb-3">
                Are AI-generated reviews always included?
              </h3>
              <p class="text-gray-600">
                Yes! AI-powered match reviews are automatically generated for
                post-match reports. They provide personalized feedback based on
                each player's performance, champion choice, and match context.
                The reviews are designed to be constructive and help players
                improve.
              </p>
            </div>

            <div class="border border-gray-200 rounded-lg p-6">
              <h3 class="font-semibold text-gray-900 mb-3">
                Can I track players from different regions in the same server?
              </h3>
              <p class="text-gray-600">
                Yes! You can subscribe to players from any supported League of
                Legends region. Just make sure to specify the correct region
                when subscribing.
              </p>
            </div>

            <div class="border border-gray-200 rounded-lg p-6">
              <h3 class="font-semibold text-gray-900 mb-3">
                How many players can I track?
              </h3>
              <p class="text-gray-600">
                There's no hard limit on the number of players you can track,
                but we recommend keeping it reasonable to avoid channel spam.
              </p>
            </div>

            <div class="border border-gray-200 rounded-lg p-6">
              <h3 class="font-semibold text-gray-900 mb-3">
                Why am I not getting post-match reports?
              </h3>
              <p class="text-gray-600">
                Post-match reports are generated after games end. Very short
                games (usually under 5 minutes) or remakes might not generate
                reports. The reports typically appear 2-5 minutes after a match
                ends.
              </p>
            </div>

            <div class="border border-gray-200 rounded-lg p-6">
              <h3 class="font-semibold text-gray-900 mb-3">Is my data safe?</h3>
              <p class="text-gray-600">
                Scout only stores the minimum data necessary to provide
                notifications: Riot IDs, aliases, and Discord channel
                information. We don't store personal information or match
                history beyond what's needed for reports.
              </p>
            </div>
